On January 3, 2012, the President signed several laws. These include the reauthorization and amendment of the Belarus Democracy Act of 2004, the designation of a United States Postal Service facility in Little Ferry, New Jersey, as the Sergeant Matthew J. Fenton Post Office, the extension of the authority to redact personal and sensitive information in the financial disclosure reports of judicial officers and employees, the designation of a property in Jackson, Tennessee, as the M.D. Anderson Plaza, the implementation of expedited security screening services for members of the Armed Forces, the authorization of appropriations for U.S. intelligence-related activities, the requirement for a study on the impact of the failure of insured depository institutions, the designation of a United States Postal Service facility in Staten Island, New York, as the Sergeant Angel Mendez Post Office, and the doubling of maximum civil penalties for violations of Federal pipeline safety laws.